      "description": "cols - The number of rows and columns. Rows are horizontal lines; Columns are vertical lines. Two rows by two columns makes a square or rectangle. For example, one row and two columns makes a single line if Connectivity is set to Rows.\t\nFor NURBS and Bzier surfaces, the Rows & Cols refer to the surface hull construction, and as such, the number of Rows and Cols should not be less than the Order in U or V.",
